        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 4:02PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Coushatta, or 18 miles east of Mansfield. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Coushatta, Evelyn, Lake End, Grand Bayou, Hanna, Rambin, and
Armistead.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
